  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy reveal visible">
          <div class="eyebrow">LLM Reliability SDK</div>
          <h1><span class="gradient">Verified Failover</span> for LLM Applications</h1>
          <p class="lead" style="margin-top:20px;">
            Correctover validates every response contract before your application trusts it—schema, meaning, latency, cost, integrity, and identity—then self-heals in microseconds with zero network overhead.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#pricing">pip install correctover</a>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="console.html">View Live Benchmarks</a>
          </div>

          <div class="install-chip">
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <span>$ pip install correctover</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-panel reveal visible">
          <div class="panel-inner">
            <div class="mini-terminal">
              <div class="terminal-head"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
              <div class="terminal-body">
                <div><span class="terminal-accent">from</span> correctover <span class="terminal-accent">import</span> Guard</div>
                <div><span class="terminal-ok">guard</span> = Guard(<span class="terminal-num">verified_failover=True</span>)</div>
                <div>response = <span class="terminal-ok">guard</span>.call(<span class="terminal-num">llm_request</span>)</div>
                <br />
                <div>✔ Schema Validation</div>
                <div>✔ Semantic Equivalence</div>
                <div>✔ Latency Compliance</div>
                <div>✔ Cost Guardrails</div>
                <div>✔ Content Integrity</div>
                <div>✔ Identity Verification</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="stats-strip">
              <div class="stat-pill">
                <b>22µs</b>
                <span>P50 diagnosis latency</span>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-pill">
                <b>0.4µs</b>
                <span>Circuit breaker P50</span>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-pill">
                <b>177,582</b>
                <span>Telemetry rec/s</span>
              </div>
              <div class="stat-pill">
                <b>~375 KB</b>
                <span>SDK footprint</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="problem">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="eyebrow reveal">Reliability Gap</div>
        <h2 class="reveal">HTTP 200 Is Not Enough</h2>
        <p class="lead reveal">
          Your provider can return success while the application still fails. Correctover catches the hidden failures standard retries and status-code checks miss.
        </p>

        <div class="problem-grid">
          <div class="card problem-card reveal">
            <div class="problem-icon">≠</div>
            <h3>Semantically Wrong</h3>
            <p>The response parses, but the meaning drifts from user intent or expected behavior.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card problem-card reveal">
            <div class="problem-icon">⏱</div>
            <h3>Too Slow to Use</h3>
            <p>A valid answer arriving after your latency budget is still an application failure.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card problem-card reveal">
            <div class="problem-icon">$</div>
            <h3>Cost Blowouts</h3>
            <p>Token spikes and provider variance silently break unit economics without tripping transport errors.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card problem-card reveal">
            <div class="problem-icon">⚠</div>
            <h3>Unsafe or Untrusted</h3>
            <p>Content integrity violations, identity mismatch, or malformed output can poison downstream systems.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="solution">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="eyebrow reveal">Contract Validation</div>
        <h2 class="reveal">Six Dimensions. One Verified Decision.</h2>
        <p class="lead reveal">
          Correctover evaluates every LLM response against a multidimensional contract before it reaches production logic.
        </p>

        <div class="validation-grid">
          <div class="card validation-card reveal">
            <div class="check"></div>
            <h3>Schema Validation</h3>
            <p>Ensure structure, types, and required fields are exactly what your application expects.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card validation-card reveal">
            <div class="check"></div>
            <h3>Semantic Equivalence</h3>
            <p>Verify the response preserves intended meaning, not just syntactic correctness.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card validation-card reveal">
            <div class="check"></div>
            <h3>Latency Compliance</h3>
            <p>Reject responses that arrive outside your operational SLOs even when transport succeeds.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card validation-card reveal">
            <div class="check"></div>
            <h3>Cost Guardrails</h3>
            <p>Enforce budget-aware execution with token and spend boundaries built into runtime validation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card validation-card reveal">
            <div class="check"></div>
            <h3>Content Integrity</h3>
            <p>Protect against partial corruption, unsafe content, and output drift that breaks downstream trust.</p>
